id=acc
domain=vr25
name=Advanced Charging Controller (ACC)
version=v2025.5.18-6.4-rc1
versionCode=202505218
author=VR25 (community stable)
description=[6.4-rc1 (pre-release) -- SAFETY + DIAGNOSTICS. No change to the 6.2/6.3 resume logic and no change to how charging is controlled on a working device; every change is stricter, append-only, a clamp, or diagnostic. (1) A charging switch is locked only after a SUSTAINED hold -- current is sampled 3x and a switch that stops then re-arms (e.g. MediaTek current_cmd on Xiaomi/HyperOS klee) is rejected -- in BOTH the daemon auto-locker AND the manual scanner; this stops the overcharge at its source, not after a breach. (2) The breach watchdog is gated on charger PRESENT, not online: an input-cut switch drives */online to 0 while the cable is still attached, which used to blind the watchdog on exactly those devices. (3) Out-of-range pause/resume/shutdown values now fail safe, and pause/resume are forced into one unit domain (no mixed mV/% never-pause). (4) Pure throttle nodes (step_charging, restricted_charging, cool_mode/down, system_temp_level, temp_cool) are excluded from switch candidates. (5) `acca --state` reads battery/uevent in one atomic snapshot and reports a real statusTrust (was always "unknown") plus a native-limit block for Pixel/Tensor. Plus uA/mA unit threshold unified, flip_sw on=100 re-arm, dead read-only qpnp node dropped, OPLUS charge node added. Existing configs unchanged; auto-migrate, no command.] Extend your battery's service life by controlling charging current, temperature, and voltage. Any root solution is supported. The installation is always "systemless". Works on Android and KaiOS.
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VR-25/acc/master/module.json
